The paper deals with the cryptographic primitive of Oblivious RAM (ORAM) and its distributed variant, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves techniques related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS) to achieve efficient ORAM schemes. The use of hashing schemes and linear computations suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC) may also be relevant sub-categories.
